    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4062cf35_b9093bb6",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/opengl/EmuglBackendList.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 60,
      "author": {
        "id": 1087303
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-07T18:27:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "At this moment we just need an experimental config. Later we might switch to ANGLE under translator by default, once we solve all performance issues. So yes, this code is \"temporary\".",
      "parentUuid": "f6cb7689_50f2fa49",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 58,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 60,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "845ea8d63582769e4a44569aeca9a97e7805851c",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "020ba5b7_31b8591c",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/opengl/EmuglBackendList.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 60,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-07T18:34:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, then why not switch to ANGLE under translator by default, take the performance hit, and avoid taking the hit of more complex GPU configs and then refactoring \"temporary\" code in the future?\n\nThe configs we make users use ANGLE on are usually very limited by the host GPU fill rate anyway; we are not using ANGLE on GTX 970 or Quadro K2200.\n\nQuestion is if the performance hit is 20% regardless of how fast the underlying host GPU; try a performance comparison of ANGLE using a Intel HD 4000 before and after putting it under the translator. (There\u0027s also a Intel HD 4600 paird with a similarly slow Quadro K1100M on the laptop next to my desk). If it doesn\u0027t make much difference, we should definitely just switch it to be under translator by default.",
      "parentUuid": "4062cf35_b9093bb6",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 58,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 60,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "845ea8d63582769e4a44569aeca9a97e7805851c",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1d24c73a_bdd7ce88",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/opengl/EmuglBackendList.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 60,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-07T18:39:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Absolute numbers also matter too. If Antutu goes from 15 to 12 FPS, that\u0027s not really an earth-shattering performance drop.\n\nOn the other hand, If Antutu goes from 60 to even 50, that is much more noticeable and worse (But the GPU needs to be pretty damn good to even hit 60 on Antutu already; we wouldnt make users use ANGLE in that situation). As another example, if 1080p30 was achieveable and now it\u0027s not achievable, also bad. Etc.",
      "parentUuid": "020ba5b7_31b8591c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 58,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 60,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "845ea8d63582769e4a44569aeca9a97e7805851c",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
